<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sebastian Stan is back to work on his latest Marvel project, as Hollywood bounces back from the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>

<p>But the Romanian-American actor is still taking necessary precautions against the coronavirus at work.</p>

<p>He rocked a sweet blue leather jacket Friday night, as he masked up in a matching blue surgical mask, between takes on the set of The Falcon and the Winter Soldier in Atlanta.</p>

<p>COVID protocol: Sebastian Stan rocked a sweet blue leather jacket Friday night, as he masked up in a matching blue surgical mask, between takes on the set of The Falcon and the Winter Soldier in Atlanta</p>

<p>The 38-year-old was in character as Bucky Barnes (aka Winter Soldier), the comic book character he originated onscreen in the 2011 blockbuster Captain America: The First Avenger.</p>

<p>His jacket featured only one sleeve, while revealing his character's high-tech prosthetic arm/killing machine. </p>

<p>The Falcon and the Winter Soldier was set to premiere last month on the streaming platform, but it was ultimately postponed to next year, amid the global pandemic.</p>

<p>Stan stars in the upcoming Disney+ miniseries alongside Anthony Mackie, 42, who revives his role as Sam Wilson (aka Falcon).</p>

